The '''Flora School''', at 82744 Church St. in [[Flora, Oregon]], is a historic [[Bungalow/craftsman architecture|Bungalow/craftsman]]-style school that was built in 1915. It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1997.<ref name=nris/>  It was deemed significant for association with education and the community, and for its architecture.  It is a {{convert|52|x|80|ft|m|adj=on}} building that, at the time of its 1996 NRHP nomination, had been vacant since 1977 and then had a weathered condition.<ref name=nrhpdoc>{{cite web|url=http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NRHP/Text/97000579.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Flora School |author=Vanessa Thew Thompson |date=November 26, 1996 |publisher=National Park Service}} and [http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NRHP/Photos/97000579.pdf accompanying 13 photos]</ref>

